<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM10.7">
<l>kuraikaṭalai yaṭalampāṉ maṟuka veytu kulaikaṭṭi maṟukaraiyai yataṉā lēṟi</l>
<l>yerineṭuvē larakkaroṭu milaṅkai vēnta ṉiṉṉuyirkoṇ ṭavaṉṟampik karacu mīntu</l>
<l>tirumakaḷō ṭiṉitamarnta celvaṉ ṟaṉṉait tillainakart tiruccitra kūṭan taṉṉuḷ</l>
<l>ḷaracamarntā ṉaṭicūṭu maracai yallā laracāka veṇṇēṉmaṟ ṟaracu tāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>I shall not consider [any] other kingdom as a kingdom</l>
<l>other than the kingdom of adorning the feet of</l>
<l rend="indent">Him who sat in governance inside Tiruccitrakūṭam in the town of Tillai,</l>
<l rend="indent">the Lord, who, having shot a victorious arrow so that the roaring sea whirled,</l>
<l rend="indent">built a bridge [across it], reached the other shore by means of that [bridge],</l>
<l rend="indent">took the sweet life of the king of Laṅkā</l>
<l rend="indent">along with [those] of the rakshasas with blazing long spears,</l>
<l rend="indent">gave the kingdom to his younger brother [and] sweetly sat with the auspicious Lady.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
